  "texts": [
    "This seems inconsistent with the forecast mentioned earlier by the same group.Note that the forecasts are all conditional on \"human scientific activity continu[ing] without major negative disruption.",
    "\"1 3 That being said, there may be cases where humans regard something as morally desirable which is actually a moral catastrophe.",
    "Also, in this decision situation, we care about the overall best course of action.",
    "Hence, the deontological distinction between obligatory and supererogatory actions is not relevant.1 3 In that sense, you could call AI alignment a \"pre-paradigmatic science\" in the sense of Kuhn[37].",
    "While not discussed by Hubinger, someone who is not convinced that AGI would have a strong tendency to pursue convergent instrumental goals such as power-seeking could also be optimistic that partially aligned agents will avoid catastrophic risks.1 3 As the list of training goals reveals, an aligned AI may be one which -in some sense -does not pursue any goals.1 3"
